<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Oh man, I want to tell you about the funniest =
Money Stuff item of, like, summer 2024. Here=E2=80=99s what it will be:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Elon Musk is going to ask Tesla Inc.=
=E2=80=99s board of directors to change its state of incorporation from Del=
aware, which just <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
34321970.285393/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzI=
wMjQtMDEtMzEvZWxvbi1tdXNrLWlzLW92ZXJwYWlkP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMTIyNF9NT05FWVNUVU=
ZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDIxM=
iZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB14e13500" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
">  invalidated Musk=E2=80=99s $55 billion pay package</a>, <a href=3D"http=
s://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34321970.285393/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY=
mxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDItMDEvdGV4YXMtdGVtcHRzLXRl=
c2xhP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMTIyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJ=
jZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDIxMiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607=
f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3ad70611" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  to Texas</a>, which loves Musk an=
d is begging him to move and would probably let him pay himself whatever he=
 wants.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Tesla=E2=80=99s board is g=
oing to be like =E2=80=9Csure yes of course, whatever you want.=E2=80=9D</l=
i>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Then Tesla will ask shareholders to =
vote to approve the relocation, as Musk <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/34321970.285393/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9lbG9ubXVza=
y9zdGF0dXMvMTc1MjkyMjA3MTIyOTcyMjk5MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa9d2a443" it=
emprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #=
ccc;"> has already said it will do</a>.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: =
5px;">Some shareholders will sue Tesla, asking a=C2=A0<em>Delaware=C2=A0</e=
m>court to stop Tesla from moving.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;"=
>They might win?=C2=A0</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It cannot really be the case that a Delaware c=
ourt can stop any Delaware corporation from moving its state of incorporati=
on to Texas. But it <em>might=C2=A0</em>be the case that a Delaware court c=
ould stop=C2=A0<em>Tesla=C2=A0</em>from moving to Texas.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Today <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/34321970.285393/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9idXNpbmVzcy9lbG=
9uLW11c2staXNudC10aGUtb25seS1iaWxsaW9uYWlyZS1maWdodGluZy1kZWxhd2FyZXMtZ3Jpc=
C1vbi11LXMtYnVzaW5lc3MtZTlmZTI5OWE_bW9kPWhwX2xlYWRfcG9zMQ/607f07ceef4b8524a=
319a23cB05133eec" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"=
_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;"> the Wall Street Journal has a story</a> previewi=
ng this news:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Three powerful shareholders are trying to loos=
en Delaware=E2=80=99s long-held grip over public companies.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Tripadvisor, under media executive Greg Maffei=
, wants to reincorporate in Nevada, over the objection of minority sharehol=
ders. Billionaire Barry Diller is awaiting a ruling that could relax Delawa=
re=E2=80=99s scrutiny of transactions like the 2020 split of some of his on=
line businesses. And Elon Musk, who reincorporated Twitter as X in Nevada l=
ast year, has said he would ask shareholders about reincorporating Tesla in=
 Texas.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The stuff about Musk and Tesla and Texas, sure=
. But I want to focus on TripAdvisor, because that is the real preview of w=
hat could happen with Tesla. TripAdvisor Inc.,=C2=A0and its parent company,=
 Liberty Tripadvisor Holdings Inc., are Delaware public=C2=A0companies that=
 are run and controlled by Greg Maffei, who has supervoting stock and does,=
 uh, fun stuff with his voting power. He gets sued by shareholders sometime=
s, and apparently wanted to reincorporate his companies to Nevada to get su=
ed less: Nevada=E2=80=99s corporate law seems to be friendlier to corporate=
 officers and controlling shareholders, with =E2=80=9Cbroad protections for=
 directors and officers in many cases that Delaware wouldn=E2=80=99t, inclu=
ding involving improper personal gain,=E2=80=9D according to the Journal.</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And the companies=E2=80=99 boards of directors=
 considered moving to Nevada, and the directors decided it was a good idea,=
 and they=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/343=
21970.285393/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9peHZpZXdlci9peC5odG1sP2RvYz0vQXJjaG=
l2ZXMvZWRnYXIvZGF0YS8xNTI2NTIwLzAwMDA5NTAxNzAyMzAxNDUzMi90cmlwLTIwMjMwNDI2L=
mh0bSNwcm9wb3NhbF8z/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB653833d6" itemprop=3D"StoryLin=
k" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-=
decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color:=
 #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">asked shareh=
olders to vote</a> to approve the move, and the shareholders approved. Well=
, <em>Maffei=C2=A0</em>approved, and he has supervoting shares; a majority =
of the independent shareholders voted against the proposals to move, but th=
ey passed anyway.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But some shareholders sued to stop=C2=A0Maffei=
 from doing=C2=A0this. Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/34321970.285393/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N1bWVudHMvdX=
NlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL3JmdjRLbHE2N253dy92MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0bd3e=
19a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> their complaint</a>.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#foot=
note-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !=
important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;=
">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0The argument is essentially:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Under Delaware corporate law, a compa=
ny=E2=80=99s board of directors and controlling shareholder have fiduciary =
duties to the ordinary=C2=A0shareholders, and they can=E2=80=99t do somethi=
ng =E2=80=94=C2=A0even something otherwise legal, like reincorporating to N=
evada =E2=80=94=C2=A0if it violates their fiduciary duties.</li>=09<li styl=
e=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Where the board and controlling shareholder have =
a conflict of interest =E2=80=94=C2=A0where they get something from a trans=
action at the expense of ordinary shareholders =E2=80=94=C2=A0then Delaware=
 will review the transaction for =E2=80=9Centire fairness=E2=80=9D: The tra=
nsaction is a breach of fiduciary duties, and so not allowed, unless the co=
urt finds that it is =E2=80=9Centirely fair=E2=80=9D to the ordinary shareh=
olders.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Maffei and his board of di=
rectors get something out of moving to Nevada (they get to not be sued for =
doing creative stuff with their control of the companies), and this comes a=
t the expense of the ordinary shareholders (they don't get to sue if Maffei=
 does creative stuff to them).<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote=
-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !impo=
rtant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">But the ordinary shareholders wer=
e not compensated for this, and voted against it, and the board did not hav=
e a special committee of independent directors to consider the move: It jus=
t did what Maffei wanted. So=C2=A0the move is surely not =E2=80=9Centirely =
fair=E2=80=9D to them.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">So a Delawa=
re court can and should stop TripAdvisor and Liberty TripAdvisor from movin=
g to Nevada, so that Delaware can continue to keep an eye on Maffei for the=
 benefit of the ordinary shareholders.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And that kind of=C2=A0<em>is=C2=A0</em>how Del=
aware law works. In fact, this is more or less the same reasoning that a De=
laware court applied last month to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/34321970.285393/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW=
9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDEtMzEvZWxvbi1tdXNrLWlzLW92ZXJwYWlkP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyM=
TIyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0=
bV90ZXJtPTI0MDIxMiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23c=
C14e13500" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;">  strike down Musk=E2=80=99s pay package</a>:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Tesla=E2=80=99s directors =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0and Musk, who the court found is the =E2=80=9Ccontrolling shareholder=
=E2=80=9D of Tesla even though he doesn=E2=80=99t own supervoting shares or=
 a majority of the stock =E2=80=94=C2=A0have fiduciary duties to Tesla=E2=
=80=99s ordinary shareholders.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Con=
flicted transactions need to be entirely fair to those shareholders.</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Musk got something out of his pay pack=
age (options worth more than $55 billion),=C2=A0at the expense of ordinary =
shareholders (who got diluted).</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Th=
e ordinary shareholders=C2=A0<em>did=C2=A0</em>actually vote to approve the=
 pay package, but the judge found that their vote was not fully informed.</=
li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">And the judge found that the pay pa=
ckage wasn=E2=80=99t entirely fair to shareholders =E2=80=94=C2=A0basically=
, Musk wasn=E2=80=99t worth what he was paid =E2=80=94=C2=A0so she blocked =
it.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And Maffei doesn=E2=80=99t really argue agains=
t this framework. Instead, his lawyers argue that there is no conflict of i=
nterest here, because Maffei and the directors want to move to Nevada for g=
ood corporate governance reasons, and they aren=E2=80=99t getting any perso=
nal benefits. From their <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com=
/click/34321970.285393/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N1bWVudHMvdXNlcnMv=
aXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL3I2ZWZrWlhpWk0uTS92MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9c5ee027" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;"> motion to dismiss</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Plaintiffs ask this Court to do something that=
 has never been done before =E2=80=94 prevent a corporation from leaving th=
e state of Delaware notwithstanding its undisputed compliance with the prov=
isions of the [Delaware General Corporation Law]=C2=A0that allow the corpor=
ation to do so.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Section 266 of the DGCL gives corporations the=
 right to leave Delaware and reorganize under the laws of another jurisdict=
ion. Plaintiffs seek to limit that right, if not do away with it altogether=
. Specifically, Plaintiffs argue that where, as here, a corporation decides=
 to move from Delaware to a state that potentially provides officers and di=
rectors with greater protection from future litigation based on conduct tha=
t has not yet occurred =E2=80=94 and thus claims that do not yet exist=E2=
=80=94the Court should enjoin the move as a breach of the directors=E2=80=
=99 (and, in this case, an alleged controller=E2=80=99s) fiduciary duty.=C2=
=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Because there=E2=80=99s no conflict, Maffei ar=
gues, the Delaware court should defer to the board=E2=80=99s business judgm=
ent rather than conduct its own review of the fairness of moving to Nevada:=
</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Plaintiffs theorize that the Directors were co=
nflicted because there might be future board decisions that might give rise=
 to litigation claims and such claims might survive a motion to dismiss in =
Delaware, but not in Nevada. As explained below, Plaintiffs=E2=80=99 specul=
ation is too hypothetical and remote to constitute a unique benefit today. =
The Amended Complaint does not allege any existing or even inchoate litigat=
ion claim that the Conversions would extinguish. Plaintiffs=E2=80=99 hypoth=
esized conflict arises from the mere possibility that the Boards might take=
 some unidentified action in the future=E2=80=94after the Companies have mo=
ved to Nevada =E2=80=94 that could give rise to a future stockholder claim.=
 But the risk of a future unknown stockholder claim is one every board face=
s and is not sufficient to require entire fairness review, much less preven=
t a corporation from electing to move to another state. =E2=80=A6=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Amended Complaint does not contain factual=
 allegations supporting a reasonably conceivable inference that the Directo=
rs or Maffei have a financial interest in the transaction or that Maffei wo=
uld obtain some unique benefit from the Conversions.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And that=E2=80=99s reasonable. But later this =
year, when we talk about Elon Musk moving Tesla to Texas, <em>he </em>won=
=E2=80=99t be able to make that argument. He will have a=C2=A0<em>very very=
 clear financial interest=C2=A0</em>in the transaction: A Delaware court ju=
st struck down his $55 billion pay package, and even before that he was <a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34321970.285393/aHR0c=
HM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDEtMTYvbW9yZ2Fu=
LXN0YW5sZXktbGVha2VkLXNvbWUtYmxvY2stdHJhZGVzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMTIyNF9NT05FWVN=
UVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MD=
IxMiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB56155b6e" ite=
mprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"colo=
r: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bor=
der-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #c=
cc;"> going around posting</a> that he wanted another enormous stock grant =
so that he can control at least 25% of Tesla=E2=80=99s stock. And if he can=
=E2=80=99t get it in Delaware, he=E2=80=99ll go to Texas.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I am sure that, when Tesla actually asks its s=
hareholders to approve reincorporating in Texas, it will have good lawyers =
write=C2=A0a proxy statement emphasizing the many corporate benefits of Tex=
as, the importance of attracting and retaining talent=C2=A0and the value th=
at Musk provides to Tesla. I don=E2=80=99t even think that will be wrong; I=
 think there is something odd, and perhaps shareholder-unfriendly, about a =
Delaware judge striking down a pay package that Tesla=E2=80=99s board=C2=A0=
<em>and shareholders=C2=A0</em>thought was a good idea. I just think that E=
lon Musk is not the most carefully lawyered guy in the world in his persona=
l statements, and he will have made =E2=80=94=C2=A0he has already made =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0a very clear record proving that he wants to move to Texas=C2=
=A0<em>so that he can make Tesla give him $75 billion worth of stock.</em><=
a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transp=
arent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So shareholders will go to the Delaware=C2=A0j=
udge saying =E2=80=9CElon Musk tried to pay himself $55 billion, and you st=
opped him from doing that because it was unfair to shareholders, and now he=
 is trying to move Tesla to Texas so that he can (1) get rid of you and (2)=
 pay himself=C2=A0<em>$75 billion</em>, so you have to stop him again.=E2=
=80=9D And I think that is an argument that the Delaware judge might find c=
ompelling? I mean, she=C2=A0<em>did=C2=A0</em>stop Musk from paying himself=
 $55 billion. Presumably this move will be even more offensive.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And Tesla=C2=A0<em>is=C2=A0</em>a Delaware cor=
poration, so it=C2=A0<em>is=C2=A0</em>subject to the orders of the=C2=A0Del=
aware court, even if those orders are =E2=80=9Cwhere do you think you=E2=80=
=99re going? Get back here you little scamp!=E2=80=9D And so maybe Tesla re=
ally can=E2=80=99t leave?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway, that=E2=80=99s the news from six month=
s from now, and I suppose when it actually happens I will just write some c=
omical imagined dialogue for Musk and say =E2=80=9Csee previous column.=E2=
=80=9D There are some risks to this thesis:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Musk could appeal=C2=A0the decision ab=
out his compensation and win, and then he might lose interest in moving to =
Texas.=C2=A0I kind of think that he=E2=80=99ll want to move even if he wins=
 on appeal, though.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Maffei could w=
in such a comprehensive victory in the TripAdvisor case that nobody will ev=
en be able to argue that a court can stop Musk from leaving Delaware, so Te=
sla will=C2=A0just leave with no problem.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom=
: 5px;">Maffei could=C2=A0<em>lose=C2=A0</em>so comprehensively that Musk=
=E2=80=99s lawyers will tell him =E2=80=9Cyou=E2=80=99ve got no shot at lea=
ving Delaware, don=E2=80=99t even bother,=E2=80=9D and he=E2=80=99ll believ=
e them and give that up. I assign 0% probability to this one.</li>=09<li st=
yle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Moving to Texas might be a thing that Musk <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34321970.285393/aHR0cH=
M6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9lbG9ubXVzay9zdGF0dXMvMTc1MjkyMjA3MTIyOTcyMjk5MA/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cCa9d2a443" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">posts about</a> but does not actually =
plan to do?</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t know; I think it=E2=80=99s gon=
na happen. Last week <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/34321970.285393/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIw=
MjQtMDItMDkvbXVzay1zLW5ldXJhbGluay1kaXRjaGVzLWRlbGF3YXJlLXJlaW5jb3Jwb3JhdGV=
