V0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDAyMTImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c=
3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc8cc835b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Musk moved Neuralink Co=
rp.</a>, his brain implant company, from Delaware to Nevada, and he previou=
sly moved Twitter to Nevada (and renamed it X). Those deals were easy, thou=
gh: Those are private companies with smallish groups of shareholders, none =
of whom are all that jazzed to sue Elon Musk, so he can kind of do what he =
wants. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34321970.28=
5393/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDEtMz=
