13500" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;"> said last month</a> that =E2=80=9Cthere is something awkwar=
d about a judge second-guessing the CEO compensation decisions of the board=
 of directors of a $600 billion company, even if, yes, it=E2=80=99s the boa=
rd of Tesla.=E2=80=9D But that is nothing compared to how awkward it will b=
e for a Delaware judge to=C2=A0<em>prevent the company from leaving Delawar=
e=C2=A0</em>because Musk doesn=E2=80=99t like Delaware judges. It seems lik=
e the world can=E2=80=99t really work that way, that Delaware can=E2=80=99t=
=C2=A0<em>really=C2=A0</em>prevent its companies from leaving. And yet =E2=
=80=A6=C2=A0maybe? It=E2=80=99s gonna be a fun time here at Money Stuff whe=
n it happens.</p>
